pageContext.description: Dimensions: EL 157.5mm; EWe 95mm; Wbt 38.8mm; max T 12mm,Typology: no trace of face bev. or e. bev.; body edges qt. crsip but no flanges; double-facetted on one side - poss. not orig. feature; butt prob. approx. orig. shape.,Condition: crack across one face - probably ancient damage; part of edge poss. near intact but reworked recently - dull brown, not particularly stays: notches prob. anc. dam; little bit at butt and all down sides brown - reworked; band of recent cuts across either side,Attached Material: small patches of orangey brown soil
pageContext.surface: Undulating surface, varied dull to pale green - some pock scars; sides and edges brown banded stains across haft and from modern hafting.
pageContext.collection: Worthing Museum,582,apparently received in 1937, source unknown
